Great British Menu - Season 11, Episodes 26 to 30




South East

This week, three of the most exciting talents from London and the south east region are competing for a place in the national finals. Head chef Mark Froydenlund runs Marcus Wareing's two-star restaurant and is back to make amends for his early exit from the competition last year. Newcomer Russell Bateman is head chef at The Grove in Hertfordshire and is hoping to impress. The third chef is another newcomer, Ronnie Murray, who heads up the Hix Restaurant group. He is out to emulate the success of his boss Mark Hix, a former GBM banquet winner.




Original Air Dates: 03-Oct-2016 to 07-Oct-2016
